narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: I learned about the history of computing and how technology evolved over time.
An Introduction to the history of Computer Science as a field and an industry; we learned about important inventions that were precursors to modern machines.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: Strengths: Professor Fischer is extremely knowledgeable about the content and extremely nice. He is always responding to student emails and is extremely approachable. Weaknesses: None

Strengths: Teaching Assistant was always willing to help and made himself available. Material was occasionally interesting.

Weaknesses: Professor focused a lot on specific topics which were not entirely clear to the class. Lectures were also quite boring and lacked any excitement whatsoever. Students would frequently not pay attention as the material presented was identical to the readings and there was no additional depth added.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: I would recommend this course if the student wants to be a part of small computer science seminar.

I would recommend for a student to complete all the readings but not take the course. Student presentations were a highlight of the class, but other than that, this was not an entertaining class and lectures were a struggle to get through.
